1.plot: Ring Master Dal makes Boopsie the Clown appear from a set of very large Dice.

2.plot: Ring Master Dal tries to surprise Boopsie with her Birthday present and then gets confused with the Upside Down Chair.

3.plot: Dal the Magical RingMaster discusses the recipe for Success and introduces Tharpo the Juggler.

3.plot: Ring Master Dal uses different size balls to illustrate the importance of adult friends. Mother Goose introduces "Goosie" her friend.

4.title: Anti Smoking and Another Mother Goose Story
4.plot: Ring Master Dal explains the dangers of smoking and second hand smoke and Mother Goose tells another great story.

6.title: Say "NO" to Pressure and Mother Goose Sings
6.plot: Ring Master Dal teaches the importance of resisting Peer Pressure - and Mother Goose Sings.

9.plot: Boopsie and Clown does her own magic trick with Red Sock and White Sock - then The Bookworm talks about stamps.

10.title: Rope Trick and Balloon Blow Up
10.plot: Ring Master Dal shows Charlie the Rope Trick and then how to make balloon animals.

11.plot: Boopsie the Clown plays "One Fish Two Fish" with audience along with The Bookworm as she introduces "Webster" her talking dictionary.

12.plot: Ring Master Dal tries to confuse the kids with telling them they have the wrong colored handkerchiefs.

13.plot: Ring Master Dal introduces a new illusion with a new Assistant - Heather. Then Ring Master Dal plays musical Hats with studio guests.

1.title: Red and Yellow Scarves
1.plot: Ring Master Dal and Boopsie the Clown perform a magic trick and The Why Girl discusses electricity.

2.title: John Quincy Adams and Leaders Plus The Warp Zone
2.plot: Ring Master Dal and Boopsie talk about Leaders, Why Girl talks about flowers and Ring Master Dal takes a kid thru the Warp Zone.

3.title: Sharing, Chocolate and magical Dice
3.plot: Ring Master Dal and Boopsie the Clown discuss sharing and a magical Dice - plus the Why Girl talks about why chocolate is wrapped in foil.

4.title: Gravity, snoring and sharing hearts
4.plot: Ring Master Dal and Boopsie the Clown discuss Gravity and sharing hearts, plus The Why Girl talks about snoring.

5.title: Magic Paint Can - sharing and Ozzie the Ostrich
5.plot: Boopsie chats with Ozzie the Ostrich; The Why Girl explains the days of the week and Dal and Boopsie discuss sharing with a magic paint can.

6.title: Wild Animals, Clouds and puppets
6.plot: Ring Master Dal introduces a new puppet; The Why Girl discusses Clouds and With Boopsie the Clown, Ring Master Dal brings "wild' animals into Kartoon Circus.

7.title: Kids be safe, Rain and Platapus
7.plot: Ring Master Dal explains how to be safe with Studio's Kids; The Why Girl talks about Rain and Boopsie the Clown introduces a platypus.

8.title: Torn and Restored Napkin; Egg's shape and Herman
8.plot: Ring Master Dal and Boopsie the Clown perform the "torn and restored napkin" trick; The Why Girl tells us about the shape of eggs and Boopsie introduces Herman the Elephant and discusses contribution of time.

9.title: Big Money, Apples and American Flag
9.plot: RingMaster Dal works with a young audience member and performs "big money"; The Why Girl tells why cut apples turn brown and RingMaster Dal and "Lucy" discuss being a leader.

10.title: The Broom; Hurricanes and Island Books
10.plot: Ring Master Dal along with Boopsie and Heather their assistant perform a magical broom trick; The Why Girl discusses the naming of Hurricanes and Ring Master Dal discusses the importance of Books.

11.title: Stay Healthy and Why Girl with Sneeze
11.plot: Ring Master Dal instructs kids to be active and stay healthy; and The Why Girl tells us why we sneeze.

12.title: Magic Color Blocks; Why Girl With Sky Blue and Flowers for Boopsie
12.plot: Ring Master Dal and Boopsie have magic color blocks; The Why Girl tells us why the sky is blue and Boopsie gets flowers from Ring Master Dal.

13.title: Boopsie's Birthday; Why Girl and Volcanos and The Rope Thru the Ball
13.plot: Boopsie celebrates her birthday; The Why Girl discusses Volcanos and RingMaster Dal does a rope thru the ball trick.

imdb.title: Kartoon Circus
plot: Each week, Dal the Magician will introduce magic in an educational way for young kids and then show a classic Cartoon.::Joel Stephens
